The paper deals with the fundamental limits of a biometric identification system from an information theoretic perspective, which suggests that it may fall under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses privacy and secrecy, which are related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of biometric data suggests that it may also fall under Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the analysis of the model and characterization of capacity regions suggest that it may also fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG).
